.SS ERROR SINKS
.PP
This library reports argument-processing errors to an
.B error sink
that is reponsible for delivering the error message to its
intended target.
.PP
The default error sink writes the message to
.BR stderr ,
but the target can be easily changed to suit different needs.
.PP
Use library function
.B argeater_set_error_sink
to change the error sink.
.IP
.p_set_error_sink
.PP
There are three builtin error sink functions that can be passed
to the
.B argeater_set_error_sink
function:
.IP
.p_aesink_to_stderr
.p_aesink_to_stdout
.p_aesink_to_null
.PP
Notice that the error sink functions match the data type of the
standard function
.BR vprintf ,
which could itself be used to write error messages to
.BR stdout .
.TP
.B Custom Error Sinks
This feature was added to support saving the error message to a
string variable for Bash builtin programs.
